  "reason_thou": "### 1. Understanding the Issue\n\nThe
`simplifycfg` pass is crashing with an assertion failure in
`llvm::CallBase::paramHasNonNullAttr`. The assertion,
`getArgOperand(ArgNo)->getType()->isPointerTy() && \"Argument
must be a pointer\"`, indicates that `paramHasNonNullAttr` was
called for a function argument that is not of a pointer
type.\n\nThe crash occurs while processing the provided LLVM
IR:\n```llvm\ndefine void @test9_gep_splat(i1 %X, ptr %Y)
{\nentry:\n  br i1 %X, label %if, label %else\n\nif:\n  br label
%else\n\nelse:\n  %phi = phi ptr [ %Y, %entry ], [ null, %if ]\n
%gep = getelementptr i8, ptr %phi, <2 x i64> zeroinitializer\n
call void @fn_arg_vec(<2 x ptr> %gep)\n  ret void\n}\n```\nThe
`call` instruction `call void @fn_arg_vec(<2 x ptr> %gep)` has
an argument `%gep` of type `<2 x ptr>`, which is a vector of
pointers. The `nonnull` attribute, and consequently the
`paramHasNonNullAttr` check, is defined only for scalar pointer
types, not for vectors of pointers.\n\n### 2. Analyzing `opt`'s
Log\n\nThe backtrace shows the crash happens during speculative
execution analysis within `simplifycfg`:\n1.
`simplifyCondBranch` attempts to speculatively execute the `if`
block.\n2.  This leads to `speculativelyExecuteBB`, which calls
`validateAndCostRequiredSelects`.\n3.
`validateAndCostRequiredSelects` analyzes the potential `select`
instruction that would be created for the `%phi` node: `select
i1 %X, ptr %Y, ptr null`.\n4.  It then checks if using `null` in
the `else` branch would lead to undefined behavior by calling
`passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined`.\n5.
`passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined` recursively checks the uses of
the `%phi` node. One use is the `%gep` instruction.\n6.  It then
checks the uses of `%gep`, which leads to the `call`
instruction.\n7.  Inside `passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined`, it
encounters the `call` and tries to check for a `nonnull`
attribute on the argument. It calls `paramHasNonNullAttr` on the
argument, which has the vector type `<2 x ptr>`.\n8.
`paramHasNonNullAttr` asserts that its argument must be a
pointer, which fails because the type is a vector.\n\n### 3.
Root Cause Analysis\n\nThe root cause is that
`passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined` does not correctly handle uses
that are vectors of pointers. When it encounters a `call`
instruction where the argument is a vector, it incorrectly
proceeds to check for a `nonnull` attribute. The `nonnull`
attribute is not applicable to vector types, and the checking
function `paramHasNonNullAttr` is not designed to handle them,
leading to the assertion failure.\n\nThe logic in
`passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined` should be updated to recognize
that if a `call` argument is a vector type, the `nonnull`
attribute check is not applicable.\n\n### 4. Proposed Edit
Point(s)\n\nThe fix is to add a check in
`passingValueIsAlwaysUndefined` to ensure that we only call
`paramHasNonNullAttr` for pointer-type arguments.\n\n**File**:
`llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyCFG.cpp`\n\n```cpp\n//
llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyCFG.cpp:8223\n      if
(CB->isArgOperand(&Use)) {\n        unsigned ArgIdx =
CB->getArgOperandNo(&Use);\n        // Passing null to a
nonnnull+noundef argument is undefined.\n        if
(isa<ConstantPointerNull>(C) &&\n
CB->getArgOperand(ArgIdx)->getType()->isPointerTy() &&\n
CB->paramHasNonNullAttr(ArgIdx, /*AllowUndefOrPoison=*/false))\n
return !PtrValueMayBeModified;\n        // Passing undef to a
noundef argument is undefined.\n        if (isa<UndefValue>(C)
&& CB->isPassingUndefUB(ArgIdx))\n          return true;\n
}\n```\n\nI will modify the condition to check if the argument
is a pointer type before calling `paramHasNonNullAttr`.",
